The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Corporate Briefs
																								 Radico Khaitan has entered into a joint venture agreement with NV Distillers and Ridhi Sidhi Pvt Ltd to set up a distillery at Aurangabad in Maharashtra, with a combined investment of Rs 160 crore. The new entity will be called Radico nv Distilleries Maharashtra Ltd, in which Radico will hold a 36 per cent stake. The unit will manufacture extra-neutralised alcohol, Indian-made foreign liquor and ethanol. It will also have a bottling facility.																								 Tantia Constructions Ltd has bagged six orders worth Rs 102.10 crore for construction of road links and maintenance of rail link. The orders include three projects worth around Rs 12.5 crore from the National Hydroelectric Power Corporation. 																								 NKG Infrastructure Ltd has filed a draft red-herring prospectus with Sebi to enter the capital market. The company proposes to issue 63,00,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each at a price to be decided through a 100 per cent book-building process.																								 Gayatri Projects Ltd has received a road construction order valued at Rs 154.01 crore as additional work in Jhansi, Uttar Pradesh. The company has to execute the work in two years. 																								 Nihilent, a construction and solutions integration company, has implemented LAMAT, a strategy execution and performance management product, at Demag Cranes and Components (India). Demag India is a wholly owned subsidiary of German firm Demag Cranes AG.																								 Neel Metal Products Ltd, an integrated steel processing and automotive products manufacturer, has filed a draft red herring prospectus with Sebi to issue 5,251,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each. 																								 Canara Robeco, a joint venture between Canara Bank and Robeco Group NV, has received approvals from Sebi and the RBI to start operations in India. Canara Bank and Robeco had entered into a pact in March 2007 to undertake asset management in the country.																								 Zydus Cadila has received the USFDA approval for its 200mg hydroxychloroquine sulphate tablets. The medicine is used for rheumatic arthritis.																								 Gartner Research has recognised SAP as the 2006 market leader for enterprise resource planning, customer relationship and supply chain management. 																								 GE Commercial Finance has invested $22 million in Oriental Structural Engineers Pvt Ltd. The move strengthens GEs commitment to infrastructure financing in India. ADVERTISEMENT
